quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  29,15,But we rescued him and those who were in the vessel; and we made it a sign to all men
  29,16,"And Abraham; when he said to his people, \"Worship God and fear Him. This will be best for you, if ye have knowledge"
  29,17,"Ye only worship idols beside God, and are the authors of a lie. Those whom ye worship beside God can give you no supplies: seek, then, your supplies from God; and serve Him and give Him thanks. To Him shall ye return"
  29,18,Suppose that ye treat me as a liar! nations before you have treated God's messenger as a liar; but open preaching is his only duty
  29,19,See they not how God bringeth forth creation? and then causeth it to return again? This truly is easy for God
  29,20,"SAY, Go through the earth, and see how he hath brought forth created beings. Hereafter, with a second birth will God cause them to be born again; for God is Almighty"
  29,21,"Whom He pleaseth will He chastise, and on whom He pleaseth will He have mercy, and to Him shall ye be taken back"
  29,22,"And ye shall not invalidate his power either in the Earth or in the Heaven: and, save God, ye shall have neither patron nor helper"
  29,23,"As for those who believe not in the signs of God, or that they shall ever meet him, these of my mercy shall despair, and these doth a grievous chastisement await"